\begin_layout Section
Memory configuration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gitools is a Java application, and by default it starts with the default
 memory requirements stablished by most of the Java applications (usually
 256 Megabytes).
 But most probably you will need more than the default, you will realize
 this when you obtain an exception like this:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
java.lang.OutOfMemoryException
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is a way to configure the memory limits for Gitools the same way that
 Java does, using the option 
\emph on
-Xmx
\emph default
.
 But this configuration should be specified through an enviroment variable
 called 
\emph on
GITOOLS_JAVA_OPTS
\emph default
.
 Let's see some examples of how to do this with different operating systems:
\end_layout

