Linux
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Imagine that you want to use 1024 megabytes of memory for Gitools, then
 edit the 
\emph on
~/.bashrc
\emph default
 file adding a line like this:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
export GITOOLS_JAVA_OPTS=
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

-Xmx1024m
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
